(130, 'Teen girls prepare for space launch', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_technology/~3/OyexQemnmco/index.html', 'Teenage girls have designed Africa\'s first private satellite due to launch into space in 2017. It\'s hoped it can monitor and find answers to South Africa\'s drought crisis.', 'NO_IMAGE', 'Thu, 17 Nov 2016 11:07:22 EST', 'CNN', 'technology'),
(131, 'Going to space is a real pain in the back', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_technology/~3/yQhxU27O4AM/index.html', 'A six-month stay on the International Space Station can be a pain in the back for astronauts. While they may gain up to 2 inches in height temporarily, that effect is accompanied by a weakening of the muscles supporting the spine, according to a new study.', 'NO_IMAGE', 'Tue, 08 Nov 2016 13:11:11 EST', 'CNN', 'technology'),
