(333, 'Palestinian filmmaker Rashid Masharawi: \'If we are not united we will never be free\'', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190604-perspective-rashid-masharawi-palestinian-filmmaker-gaza-strip-cinema-festival-paris', 'This week, Paris is hosting the fifth edition of its annual Palestinian Film Festival. The focus this year is Gaza and the guest of honour is director and writer Rashid Masharawi. A self-taught filmmaker who was born in a refugee camp in the Gaza Strip, Masharawi has produced a long list of works and set up a mobile cinema that brings movies to refugee camps. His films include \"Laila\'s birthday\", \"Ticket to Jerusalem\", \"Waiting\" and \"Writing on Snow\". He joined us for Perspective.', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/edition/mashrawi_en_.png', 'Tue, 04 Jun 2019 09:59:16 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(334, 'Iraq sentences two more Frenchmen to death for IS membership', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190603-iraq-two-more-french-islamic-state-group-suspects-sentenced-death', 'A Baghdad court Monday sentenced to death two more French nationals for belonging to the Islamic State group, leaving all 11 Frenchmen transferred from Syria facing the gallows in Iraq.', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/03062019-irak-justice-jihadistes-oei-etat-islamique.jpg', 'Mon, 03 Jun 2019 12:05:01 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(335, 'Second round of deadly Israeli strikes hit Syria', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190603-syria-israel-second-deadly-strikes-hit', 'Israel launched a second round of strikes against Syria in 24 hours on Sunday, state media reported, as US President Donald Trump called on Russia and Iran to â€œstop bombing the hellâ€ out of the war-torn country. ', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/20190603-israel-soldats-chars-golan-m.jpg', 'Mon, 03 Jun 2019 11:51:22 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(336, 'Iraqi court sentences two French men to death for IS group membership', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190602-iraq-france-death-penalty-group-islamic-state-macron', 'An Iraqi court sentenced two French men to death on Sunday after finding them guilty of being members of Islamic State, a prosecutor told Reuters.', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/irak_franais_condamns_mort.jpg', 'Sun, 02 Jun 2019 10:09:58 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(337, 'Great survivor Netanyahu facing fight for political future', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190531-great-survivor-netanyahu-facing-fight-political-future-israel-coalition-elections', 'Facing likely criminal charges and embroiled in a fierce dispute with a former protÃ©gÃ© that has thwarted his attempt to form a new government, Israelâ€™s Benjamin Netanyahu is facing perhaps the biggest threat yet to his political future.', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/310519_netanyahu.jpg', 'Fri, 31 May 2019 15:17:46 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(338, 'Saudi king demands firm action against â€˜criminalâ€™ Iran at Arab summit', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190531-saudi-arabias-king-salman-calls-gulf-states-use-all-means-confront-iran', 'Saudi Arabia\'s King Salman on Friday ratcheted up the rhetoric against arch-nemesis Iran, calling on Arab states to confront its \"criminal\" actions after attacks on oil installations sparked fears of a regional conflagration. ', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/saudi_king_cut.jpg', 'Fri, 31 May 2019 02:31:05 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(339, 'Israel votes... again: Netanyahu and Lieberman spar over religious right ', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20193005-debate-israel-politics-elections-netanyahu-lieberman-likud', 'Neither Israel\'s prime minister nor his far-right former defence minister Avigdor Lieberman are blinking in their showdown over whether ultra-Orthodox Jews should do military service. Is this the Jewish state\'s new political divide, between secularists and the religious? With the left fading from relevancy, we ask if this will become the new hot-button issue when Israelis vote again in September. The stakes are personal for Netanyahu: he is seeking immunity in several corruption probes. ', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/edition/israelvotesagain.jpg', 'Thu, 30 May 2019 18:04:55 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(340, 'Israel faces new election as Netanyahu fails to form coalition', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190529-israel-hold-new-election-after-pm-netanyahu-fails-form-government', 'Israeli lawmakers voted to dissolve parliament early on Thursday, paving the way for a new election after veteran Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu failed to form a coalition government before a midnight deadline. ', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/israel_cut.jpg', 'Wed, 29 May 2019 21:54:41 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
(341, 'Israel faces prospect of new elections as Netanyahu\'s coalition talks hit impasse', 'https://www.france24.com/en/20190529-israel-prospect-new-parliamentary-elections-netanyahu-coalition-talks-impasse-deadline', 'Israelis faced the increasing likelihood Wednesday of a new vote just months after an April election, with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu\'s coalition talks deadlocked hours ahead of a midnight deadline.', 'https://scd.france24.com/en/files/imagecache/france24_ct_api_medium2/article/image/benjamin-netanyahu-290519-m.jpg', 'Wed, 29 May 2019 14:56:14 GMT', 'France 24', 'middle_east'),
