(367, 'Mysterious \"attack\" on four ships, says UAE', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_meast/~3/ZKU5JuNi1T0/index.html', 'Four ships were targeted on Sunday near the strategic Emirati port of Fujairah, in what the UAE described as a \"sabotage attack.\" One was flying a UAE flag, and another the Norwegian flag. The other two were tankers owned by Saudi Arabia, which described the incident as a threat to the security of global oil supplies.', 'https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/190513101243-fujairah-oil-terminal-2016-super-169.jpg', 'NO_DATE', 'CNN', 'middle_east'),
(368, 'Syrian army \'kills terrorists\' in Idlib countryside', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_meast/~3/Mzkcxsc9lm4/index.html', 'The Syrian army is launching \"intensive strikes on dens of Jabhat al-Nusra,\" a group formerly affiliated with al Qaeda, in a village in southwestern Idlib province Sunday, Syrian state media is reporting.', 'https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/190512113959-syria-strike-2-super-169.jpg', 'NO_DATE', 'CNN', 'middle_east'),
(369, 'China\'s persecuted Uyghurs live \'freely\' in Turkey', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_meast/~3/XEqTzvgo390/index.html', 'Members of the Uyghur community in Turkey say they escaped a brutal crackdown in China and now continue to rally for missing relatives believed to be held in camps.', 'https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/190312110308-01-cnn-turkey-uyghurs-super-169.jpg', 'NO_DATE', 'CNN', 'middle_east'),
(370, 'Mina Mangal, Afghan journalist, killed in Kabul', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_meast/~3/Pbc_bWfKASA/index.html', 'A prominent Afghan journalist and parliamentary adviser has been killed in Kabul, an Interior Ministry spokesman told CNN Sunday.', 'https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/190512114842-mena-mangal-super-169.jpg', 'NO_DATE', 'CNN', 'middle_east'),
(371, 'The world is more dangerous after Iran\'s nuclear deal announcement', 'http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_meast/~3/qitn5u0SWxo/index.html', 'All the ingredients are in place for a confrontation that could be the most significant outbreak of warfare since the 2003 US-led invasion of Iraq, with some of the same players leading the charge.', 'https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/171013103510-02-hassan-rouhani-donald-trump-split-super-169.jpg', 'NO_DATE', 'CNN', 'middle_east'),
